# SKILL: AI Agent Architecture

> Source: *Building AI Agents with LLMs, RAG, and Knowledge Graphs* — Raieli & Iuculano (Packt, 2025), Chapters 4 & 9

---

## 1. The Brain-Perception-Action Framework

An LLM-based agent is composed of three core components:

```
Environment
    │
    ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  PERCEPTION (Inputs)                                     │
│  Text │ Images │ Audio │ Video │ Sensors │ Web           │
└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘
                        │
                        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  BRAIN (LLM Core)                                        │
│  Storage: short-term (context) + long-term (RAG/DB)      │
│  Reasoning: CoT, planning, reflection                    │
│  Decision Making: plan formulation → plan reflection     │
└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────┘
                        │
                        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ACTION                                                  │
│  Text output │ Tool calls │ API calls │ Embodiment       │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Four Fundamental Agent Properties
| Property | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| **Autonomy** | Operates without step-by-step human instruction |
| **Reactivity** | Responds to environment state changes |
| **Pro-activeness** | Goal-directed, not just reactive |
| **Social ability** | Communicates with humans and other agents |

