## 3. Planning Strategies

### Two Decomposition Approaches
| Method | Mechanism | Best For |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| Decomposition-first | Full plan upfront, then execute sequentially | Well-defined tasks, reduces hallucination |
| Interleaved | Generate subtask → solve → repeat | Adaptive, dynamic tasks |

### Planning Taxonomy (from literature)
| Method | Idea | Representative Works |
|--------|------|---------------------|
| Task Decomposition | Divide & conquer | CoT, ReAct, HuggingGPT |
| Multi-plan Selection | Generate multiple plans, select best | ToT, GoT, CoT-SC |
| External Planner-aided | Symbolic/neural external planner | LLM+P, LLM+PDDL |
| Reflection & Refinement | Iterative feedback loop | Reflexion, CRITIC, Self-Refine |
| Memory-aided Planning | Use past experience to inform plans | REMEMBER, MemoryBank |

### Plan Lifecycle
1. **Plan Formulation**: Decompose task into ordered subtasks
2. **Plan Reflection**: Evaluate plan (self or second model); refine before execution

